Package edu.ncsu.csc216.app_manager.model.application

Class ApplicationTest

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.app_manager.model.application.ApplicationTest
public class ApplicationTest extends Object
Tests Application class functionality and behavior. Validates the creation, state transitions, and command execution on an Application instance. Ensures exceptions are thrown in invalid scenarios and that state transitions occur correctly.
Author:
Priyanshu Dongre

  • Method Details

    • createDummyApplicationObject

      public void createDummyApplicationObject()
      Creates a dummy Application object for testing purposes. Initializes a new Application instance with a sample appId, type, summary, and notes.

    • testConstructor

      @Test public void testConstructor()
      Tests the constructor of Application. Validates that an Application cannot be created with invalid parameters, such as a null type, or empty summary. Also ensures correct exceptions are thrown when invalid inputs are provided.

    • testSetAppId

      @Test public void testSetAppId()
      Tests setting the appId for an Application. Ensures valid appId values are set correctly, while negative or zero appIds result in exceptions. Validates correct exception messages for invalid inputs.

    • testSetSummary

      @Test public void testSetSummary()
      Tests setting the summary for an Application. Ensures that a valid summary is set correctly, while empty or null summaries result in exceptions with appropriate messages.

    • testAddNotes

      @Test public void testAddNotes()
      Tests the behavior of adding notes to an Application. Verifies that notes are added properly and that the format is maintained when retrieving the notes.

    • testReviewToClosedTransition

      @Test public void testReviewToClosedTransition()
      Tests the transition of an Application from Review to Closed state. Verifies that executing the REJECT command after the Review phase correctly moves the application to the Closed state and updates the resolution.

    • testInvalidApplicationCreation

      @Test public void testInvalidApplicationCreation()
      Tests that an invalid Application object cannot be created. Verifies that invalid inputs like a zero appId and empty summary lead to the correct exception being thrown.

    • testReviewToInterviewTransition

      @Test public void testReviewToInterviewTransition()
      Tests the transition from Review to Interview state. Ensures that when an application is accepted after review, it transitions correctly to the Interview state with the proper app type and reviewer.

    • testNewApplicationAcceptingOffer

      @Test public void testNewApplicationAcceptingOffer()
      Tests the behavior of a new application progressing through various stages (Review, Interview, RefCheck, Offer) and eventually being closed after offer acceptance.

    • testRejectingNewApplication

      @Test public void testRejectingNewApplication()
      Tests rejecting a new application. This method verifies that when a reject command is executed on a new application, it transitions to the Closed state with the correct resolution and notes.

    • testWaitlistNewApplication

      @Test public void testWaitlistNewApplication()
      Tests the waitlist functionality for a new application. This method verifies that a new application can be placed on a waitlist and that the correct transitions and notes are maintained.

    • testReviewWaitlistedApplication

      @Test public void testReviewWaitlistedApplication()
      Tests reviewing a waitlisted application. This method ensures that a waitlisted application can be reviewed and transitioned back to the Review state, maintaining notes and state integrity.

    • testWaitlistApplicationAfterInterview

      @Test public void testWaitlistApplicationAfterInterview()
      Tests the transition of a waitlisted application after an interview. This method verifies that a waitlisted application can be reviewed and correctly transitions back to the Interview state with updated notes.

    • testRejectApplicationAfterInterview

      @Test public void testRejectApplicationAfterInterview()
      Tests the rejection of an application after an interview. This method verifies that when an application is rejected after an interview, it correctly transitions to the Closed state and maintains accurate notes.

    • testReopenWaitlistApplication

      @Test public void testReopenWaitlistApplication()
      Tests reopening a waitlisted application. This method verifies that a waitlisted application can be reopened successfully, transitioning back to the Review state with the appropriate notes.

    • testReopenClosedApplication

      @Test public void testReopenClosedApplication()
      Tests reopening a closed application. This method verifies that a closed application can be reopened, transitioning back to the appropriate state with the correct notes.

    • testRejectOffer

      @Test public void testRejectOffer()
      Tests the rejection of an offer on an application. This method verifies that when an offer is rejected, the application correctly transitions to the Closed state and maintains accurate notes and resolutions.

    • testToString

      @Test public void testToString()
      Tests the string representation of an Application. This method verifies that the toString() method of the Application class returns the expected formatted string representation of the application, including its state and details.
